  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Special Drawing Rights _SDR</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed activities are designed to achieve the programme objectives and are adapted to respond to the different needs and constraints in target countries. During the process of designing the project, specific attention has been focused on the capacity needs of CSOs and citizens in Kenya, Malawi and Sierra Leone on SDRs and their utilisation, budget tracking, and advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">underpinning the proposed program goal and the below activities is based on the understanding that CSOs have the potential to play a critical role in contributing to an inclusive peoples&#x2019; economic recovery, both through participation in policy making and through their unique position to organize and mobilize citizens and media to demand improved public services from the grassroots to the global level. Building the capacity of CSOs to understand what Special Drawing Rights are, so as to effectively engage in strategic dialogue with decision makers on their utilization and subsequently tracking their actual allocation and spending in their own countries will give civil society the tools needed to instigate meaningful policy change for citizens</narrative>
  </description>
